<subSubSection id="F6B2F2ADE621C03F1BD32FABC7FF4188" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572" type="description">
<paragraph id="0BC416DDFA9AE45527321FF3A64E5DDB" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572">Description</paragraph>
<paragraph id="51155DA7B22A26CC8F31C9F425AE6F5E" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572">
Body 13-34 mm long, 2-4 mm wide, radiolar crown 6-17 mm long with 13-29 pairs of radioles, thorax with 13 chaetigers and abdomen with 46-82 chaetigers. Gregarious species (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A063386846D509AAB8E51F9BA39738C9" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F5999091" captionText="Figure 10. Bispira monroi (Hartman, 1961). A) Colony in situ, B) radiolar crown, C) base of crown, ventral view, D) thorax, dorsal view, E) same, ventral view, F) same, lateral view. Scale bars: A) not scaled, B, D-F) 5 mm, C) 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.8.e57572.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/437498" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572">10</figureCitation>
A). Soft tubes constructed by fine sand. Each radiole with three purple bands without a uniform distribution pattern (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5F1276A570D04388E9E094E528F59907" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F5999091" captionText="Figure 10. Bispira monroi (Hartman, 1961). A) Colony in situ, B) radiolar crown, C) base of crown, ventral view, D) thorax, dorsal view, E) same, ventral view, F) same, lateral view. Scale bars: A) not scaled, B, D-F) 5 mm, C) 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.8.e57572.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/437498" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572">10</figureCitation>
B). Within each purple radiolar band, there is a pair of compound eyes (three pairs of eyes per radiole). Ventral margins of thick base spiralling inwards to form three whorls (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A0F780F55120DCCCB5AEC2461D883CC7" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F5999091" captionText="Figure 10. Bispira monroi (Hartman, 1961). A) Colony in situ, B) radiolar crown, C) base of crown, ventral view, D) thorax, dorsal view, E) same, ventral view, F) same, lateral view. Scale bars: A) not scaled, B, D-F) 5 mm, C) 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.8.e57572.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/437498" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572">10</figureCitation>
C). Collar with purple spots dorsally and ventrally. Thorax with purple spots anterior to each thoracic notochaetae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C03866F5153886E6A57F08623245E31D" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F5999091" captionText="Figure 10. Bispira monroi (Hartman, 1961). A) Colony in situ, B) radiolar crown, C) base of crown, ventral view, D) thorax, dorsal view, E) same, ventral view, F) same, lateral view. Scale bars: A) not scaled, B, D-F) 5 mm, C) 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.8.e57572.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/437498" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572">10</figureCitation>
D). Purple maculae between ventral shields and tori (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="946BA39D962C4AEF7541C2FE2B638E1F" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F5999091" captionText="Figure 10. Bispira monroi (Hartman, 1961). A) Colony in situ, B) radiolar crown, C) base of crown, ventral view, D) thorax, dorsal view, E) same, ventral view, F) same, lateral view. Scale bars: A) not scaled, B, D-F) 5 mm, C) 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.8.e57572.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/437498" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572">10</figureCitation>
