<subSubSection id="62B1D77C452D64D1E39B4D1FA6BCA0AB" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph id="93BACACACC874AA8FB3DB94EA035DABF" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D362102D5618266121EA63DA2BAD211B" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572">
This is the only fan worm that has been included in the invertebrate guides from the Gulf of California (
<bibRefCitation id="0EECD25A9FAA88B51CBD88504F262CEF" author="Kerstitch, A" journalOrPublisher="Sea Challengers, Monterey" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572" refId="B5999836" refString="Kerstitch, A, Bertsch, H, 2007. Sea of Cortez Marine Invertebrates, A guide for the Pacific Coast, Mexico to Peru. Sea Challengers, Monterey" title="Sea of Cortez Marine Invertebrates, A guide for the Pacific Coast, Mexico to Peru" year="2007">Kerstitch and Bertsch 2007</bibRefCitation>
). It has been reported in the Gulf of California (
<bibRefCitation id="2EDD8073F004B5BA6E36833CC767F6CC" author="Kudenov, J. D." journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572" pagination="65 - 91" refId="B5999901" refString="Kudenov, J. D., 1975. Errant polychaetes from the Gulf of California, Mexico. Journal of Natural History 9 (1): 65 - 91" title="Errant polychaetes from the Gulf of California, Mexico" volume="9" year="1975">Kudenov 1975a</bibRefCitation>
) and Pacific Panama and Costa Rica (
<bibRefCitation id="5B735BEA7A12C5EB0B83763DCE317FBE" author="Knight-Jones, P." journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572" pagination="385 - 467" refId="B5999870" refString="Knight-Jones, P., Perkins, T. H., 1998. A revision of Sabella, Bispira, and Stylomma (Polychaeta: Sabellidae. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 123: 385 - 467" title="A revision of Sabella, Bispira, and Stylomma (Polychaeta: Sabellidae" volume="123" year="1998">Knight-Jones and Perkins 1998</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
